06/12/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The chairman of Serbia-Montenegro's national council for co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal, Rasim Ljajic, called on the international community Sunday (5 December) to assist in apprehending war crimes indictee Ratko Mladic. Ljajic said Belgrade authorities are willing to apprehend the fugitive, if he is hiding in Serbia. He added however that Mladic's whereabouts are not known and that assistance from the West would be useful. (Beta - 06/12/04)
